totara
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Podocarpus totara</i>, a forest tree and its timber, mahogany(-pine); a large native forest tree prized for its timber.
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Environment
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
